values:
The factors or criteria used in the selection process are unfair because [set out your reasons for thinking that the factors or criteria used are unfair, e.g:
-- I am being scored a 4 for Performance when all my appraisals have scored at least 6 for this criterion;
-- My manager is scoring me lower than he should because he does not like me and these scores are not justified;
-- The work I have done on [insert job/task details] has not been taken into account.]

If a meaningful consultation were carried out I would not be made redundant because [List here any issues you could raise in a genuine consultation that might alter the decision to dismiss you.  See below for examples]. [Examples: 
'I could identify another role [name of role] that I am also qualified to carry out'; 
'I could tell you about an alternative way of funding my role.]

There is no reduction in the amount of work I'm doing, so it's not a redundancy. You are implementing the restructure in bad faith to remove me from the organisation because [Insert your reasons - for example:
I raised a grievance which was unfairly rejected and so you now wish to get rid of me; 
I told you about unlawful activities going on in the company and you do not want to deal with them; 
I am about to go on maternity leave and you wish to appoint someone permanently to carry out my duties.]

The redundancy consultation process is inadequate because [explain why. E.g. 'I haven’t been given an opportunity to propose an alternative structure in which my role could remain’; 
- I am not being given the chance to raise the possibility of working part-time'; 
- They're only paying lip-service to the consultation, so it's not meaningful`
- I could suggest an alternative way of funding my role'.]

There was no reduction in the amount of work that I did, so it wasn't a redundancy.  You were implementing the restructure in bad faith to remove me from the organisation because  [Insert your reasons - for example:
I raised a grievance which was unfairly rejected and so you now wish to get rid of me; 
I told you about unlawful activities going on in the company and you do not want to deal with them; 
I am about to go on maternity leave and you wish to appoint someone permanently to carry out my duties.]

The redundancy consultation process was inadequate because [explain why. E.g. 'I wasn’t given an opportunity to propose an alternative structure in which my role could remain’; 
'I wasn’t given the chance to raise the possibility of working part-time'; 
'If given the opportunity, I could have identified the role of [name of role] in the organisation that I was also qualified to carry out'; 
'I could have suggested an alternative way of funding my role'.]
